Pell said he would return to clear his name after a two-year investigation he described as characterised by &#8220;relentless character assassination&#8221;. SYDNEY Pope Francis granted top adviser Cardinal George Pell leave to return to his native Australia to face charges of sexual abuse, a Vatican spokesperson said on Thursday as Pell declared his innocence.At a news conference called hours after Australian police charged him with multiple historical sex crimes, Pell said he would return to clear his name after a two-year investigation he described as characterised by relentless character assassination . These charges strengthen my resolve and the court proceedings now offer me the opportunity to clear my name and then return here back to Rome to work, Pell said.